Tried the @beplain_global Mung Bean Pore Clay Mask and honestly? Obsessed.
It’s got mung bean extract that soothes, purifies, and de-gunks my pores—without that dry, tight feeling most clay masks leave behind.

Here’s why I loved it:
✅ Gently removes excess oil
✅ Clears clogged pores
✅ Calms irritated skin

My skin felt soft, clean, and calm after just one use. If your pores need a detox but your skin hates harsh stuff—this one’s for you 💆‍♀️

latestPosts.caption:
✨ Dark spots, dullness & uneven skin tone? This toner is my new go-to! 💛
The @axisy_official Dark Spot Correcting Glow Toner is a gentle game-changer if you’re dealing with acne marks, pigmentation, or just want that radiant, even-toned glow. 🌿

🔸 5% Niacinamide helps even out skin tone & visibly reduce dark spots.
🔸 Plant-based extracts like Squalane & Sea Buckthorn hydrate, soothe, and nourish your skin barrier.
🔸 It’s lightweight, non-sticky, and super gentle—perfect for sensitive skin like mine.

Here’s how I use it:
✨ After cleansing, I pour a few drops on my hands or a cotton pad, gently swipe it across my face (especially on those stubborn marks), and follow up with a serum + moisturizer.

Results? Brighter skin, fewer spots, and a whole lot of glow! 🍊
